text: Robert Latz (born July 15, 1930) is an American politician in the state of Minnesota. He served in the Minnesota House of Representatives from 1959–1962 and 1963–1966. He was an attorney and served as Assistant Attorney General of Minnesota from 1955 to 1958.https://www.leg.state.mn.us/legdb/fulldetail?ID=13546 ==References== Category:1930 births Category:Living people Category:Members of the Minnesota House of Representatives
